## Example 1 — Identify Domain and Range Algebraically

Identify the domain and range of:

`f(x) = sqrt(2x - 6) + 1`

For the domain, require the radicand to be nonnegative:

`2x - 6 >= 0`

`2x >= 6`

`x >= 3`

So:

* domain: `{x | x >= 3}`

Find the lower limit of the range by evaluating `f(3)`:

`f(3) = sqrt(2(3) - 6) + 1 = 1`

So:

* range: `{f(x) | f(x) >= 1}`

