## Example 5 — Graph Cube Root Functions

Graph each function and state the domain and range.

### a. `g(x) = (1/3) cuberoot(x)`

This is a vertical compression of the parent function.

Sample table:

| x  | g(x) |
| -- | ---- |
| -2 | about -0.42 |
| -1 | about -0.33 |
| 0  | 0 |
| 1  | about 0.33 |
| 2  | about 0.42 |

* domain: all real numbers
* range: all real numbers

### b. `p(x) = cuberoot(x + 5)`

This is the parent graph shifted `5` units left.

* domain: all real numbers
* range: all real numbers

### c. `q(x) = cuberoot(4 - x) + 1`

Rewrite as:

`q(x) = cuberoot(-(x - 4)) + 1`

So the graph is reflected and translated right `4` and up `1`.

* domain: all real numbers
* range: all real numbers

## Think About It

Describe the end behavior of `y = cuberoot(4 - x) + 1`.

